00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:11,080
to get them in.

836
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,481
But we knew it was worth it

837
00:33:12,801 --> 00:33:14,182
because we wanted to have those spaces

838
00:33:14,222 --> 00:33:15,202
that would challenge players.

839
00:33:15,543 --> 00:33:18,404
And we wanted to have spaces that would really allow players

840
00:33:19,105 --> 00:33:21,566
to exercise their mastery of the game.

841
00:33:24,645 --> 00:33:25,907
And reflecting on the whole project,

842
00:33:27,068 --> 00:33:28,590
and thinking about what I could do better,

843
00:33:29,491 --> 00:33:32,455
I do think that initially I was so focused

844
00:33:32,775 --> 00:33:37,040
on all of the metrics that I didn't build enough space

845
00:33:37,581 --> 00:33:39,563
in for the environment team in some of the.

846
00:33:40,575 --> 00:33:42,956
to add details to some of the street level stuff.

847
00:33:43,376 --> 00:33:45,597
And we actually did end up having to rework

848
00:33:45,637 --> 00:33:46,497
some of the street metrics.

849
00:33:46,917 --> 00:33:50,338
So after we built about half of one of the first districts,

850
00:33:50,738 --> 00:33:52,779
we realized we didn't have enough space on the streets

851
00:33:53,219 --> 00:33:54,599
to include the props that we needed

852
00:33:54,639 --> 00:33:56,339
to really make the world feel detailed enough

853
00:33:56,359 --> 00:33:57,140
to make it feel real.

854
00:33:57,840 --> 00:33:59,040
And that was one of our major goals.

855
00:33:59,080 --> 00:34:00,621
We wanted it to feel like a real space.

856
00:34:00,661 --> 00:34:01,861
We wanted it to feel real.

